items.title: Talk:Topological sorting - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Talk:Topological sorting - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
The article says 'Any DAG has a topological sort, and in fact must have many.' 
This is untrue. You can have a simple, linear DAG that has only 1 topological sort.

items.title: Dependency graph - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Dependency graph - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
If a dependency graph does not have any circular dependencies, it forms a 
directed acyclic graph, and an evaluation order may be found by topological 
sorting.
